\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5 After-Hours and Emergency Response
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Information Operations Department maintains an on-call capability for after-hours emergencies.
 Severity level alone does not constitute sufficient basis for after-hours on-call activation.
 The IT Director or the on-call designee shall activate after-hours on-call response only when a mission-critical system supporting public safety operations,
 law enforcement functions,
 or a time-bound legal or financial obligation is completely non-functional and no operational workaround exists.
 Low and Normal severity work orders are explicitly excluded from after-hours on-call activation by definition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Upon after-hours on-call activation,
 the designated on-call technician shall acknowledge the activation within thirty (30) minutes and shall commence active troubleshooting within one (1) hour.
 All after-hours timeframes are measured in continuous calendar hours from the time of activation.
 The on-call technician shall create a work order in the System of Engagement in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 Section 6.8 and shall document all actions taken during the after-hours response in the work order.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall maintain and annually review the authoritative list of systems qualifying as mission-critical for purposes of after-hours on-call activation in the System of Engagement.
 The Administrative Assistant shall maintain after-hours contact procedures and on-call rotation schedules in the System of Engagement under Assistant IT Director direction.
 The Assistant IT Director shall approve changes to the rotation schedule before publication.
 These operational details are not enumerated in this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Vendor SLA Requirements
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall ensure that any contract or service agreement governing an IT-Supported or Vendor-Managed asset entered into or renewed following the effective date of this policy includes defined vendor response and resolution commitments as a condition of the engagement.
 The Assistant IT Director shall ensure that vendor SLA terms are documented at the time of contract execution and recorded in the IT Asset Catalog entry for the applicable system,
 subject to IT Director approval.
 The Assistant IT Director shall monitor vendor SLA performance in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
